AWS Transit Gateway (TGW) is a service that acts like a central hub to connect multiple VPCs and on-premises networks together. 
Instead of creating many individual VPC peering connections (which can get messy), Transit Gateway simplifies networking by providing a 
scalable, hub-and-spoke model.

Key Features
Centralized Connectivity: Connects multiple VPCs, VPNs, and Direct Connect gateways through one hub.
Scalability: Supports thousands of VPCs and on-premises connections.
Simplified Management: Reduces the complexity of managing many peering connections.
High Performance: Uses AWS backbone for low-latency, high-bandwidth communication.
Segmentation: You can isolate traffic between VPCs using route tables.

How It Works
Create a Transit Gateway in your AWS account.
Attach VPCs, VPNs, or Direct Connect gateways to the Transit Gateway.
Configure Route Tables to control how traffic flows between attachments.
Apply Security Controls using NACLs, security groups, or firewall appliances.
